com.camerontec.util.datamodel

Interface Message

  • All Superinterfaces:
    FieldGroup, IndexedBytesFieldImporter, Nullable, OrderedCollection<Field>, OrderedCollectionOfFields, OrderedCollectionOfIntKeyed<Field>, PoolableSharedObject, Recyclable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MessageImpl, NullMessage

    public interface Message
extends IndexedBytesFieldImporter, FieldGroup, PoolableSharedObject, Recyclable
    Interface defining a managed message.

    Clients of this interface should not rely on the underlying implementation providing any thread safety guarantees unless they explicitly make such a guarantee.

    See Also:
    IndexedBytesFieldImporter, FieldGroup, Field, MessageContext, MessageRecycler

    • Method Detail

      • copy

        Message copy()
        Copy this message.

        This operation returns a deep copy of this message. That is, all contained fields and their groups (and so on) are also copied and the resultant structure is identical to this message.

        The copied message inherits this message's managed context. That is, if this is a managed message (e.g. if it was sourced from a pool) then so is the copy. If this is an un-managed message then so is the copy.

        Returns:
        The deeply copied field.

      • viewBytes

        BytesSegment viewBytes(BytesSegment segment)
        Attach the specified segment as a view over the internal byte store.

        Note that this method is potentially dangerous as it gives the caller direct access to internal storage and should be used with care. Because of this and the fact that it exist only for backwards compatibility with the legacy data model, it may be removed in a future release.

        Parameters:
        segment - The segment to attach.
        Returns:
        The attached segment.
